    "optional_reagent_smiles": [
      "O=S(=O)(O)O"
    ],
    "rationale": "This is a classic and simple example of the Hofmann-L\u00f6ffler-Freytag reaction. N-chloro-N-methylbutan-1-amine, upon treatment with acid (like sulfuric acid) and then heat or light, undergoes a 1,5-hydrogen atom transfer from the delta-carbon to the nitrogen radical. The resulting carbon radical then abstracts the chlorine atom, forming a delta-chloroamine. Subsequent intramolecular nucleophilic substitution upon treatment with base yields the final product, N-methylpyrrolidine. This example clearly demonstrates the key steps: N-halogenation, radical-mediated remote C-H functionalization (1,5-HAT), and intramolecular cyclization to form a five-membered ring.",
    "collision_avoidance_note": "The core transformation is the formation of a pyrrolidine ring from an acyclic N-haloamine via a radical C-H abstraction. This specific intramolecular C-N bond formation via a 1,5-hydrogen atom transfer is characteristic and avoids collision with other named reactions. The substrate is a simple acyclic alkylamine derivative, avoiding complex scaffolds, arenes, or other reactive functional groups that could trigger unrelated reaction classifiers."
  }
}
